```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tikz-chess}

\begin{document}
\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.5]
\chessboard[setfen="rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/8/8/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}
\end{document}
```
In this example, the `scale` parameter has been set to 0.5 to create a larger chessboard. You can adjust this value to change the size of the board. The `setfen` option is used to specify the FEN notation for the starting position of the chessboard, and the `chessboard` environment creates the actual board. The code will output a chessboard diagram with the given FEN notation.

